<0xC5><0xA0>imon Ornest: We want to gather positive energy at our concerts
What do you think will happen in less than a month?
This is one of those catastrophe messages that we people like to jump at.
With our band The Tap Tap, we’re making fun of it and saying that we’re the only band in the world that can gather enough positive energy to stop or prevent the end of the world.
In December you will also realize a unique project with three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you introduce our readers to the project?
This is a nationwide charity event that we have been planning for two years.
To do this, we want to harness the marketing potential of the Mayan calendar, whose end is forecast for December 21 at 11:10 a.m.
The day before, i.e. on December 20, three concerts will take place simultaneously in Prague, Brno and Ostrava from 9 p.m.
The end of the concerts is supposed to be around the time when the Mayan calendar ends on the Pacific island of Kiribati, which is in a 12-hour time zone ahead of us.
Who did this idea come from?
Originally probably from me, then we designed the idea together with our graphic designer Honza Augusta.
Not only do we want to gather enough positive energy to prevent the end of the world, but we also want to think together with the public about the state in which we are handing this world over to our children.
On the occasion of the end of the Mayan calendar, we have also developed a unique collection of shoes, t-shirts, bags and keychains against the end of the world, with the purchase of which people can also support us through www.e-tap.cz.
The band The Tap Tap has also recorded, together with other performers, the so-called anthem against the end of the world with the title "The end of the world falls out".
Even today, the anthem is very popular on YouTube. Will it also be heard at the benefit concerts?
Of course, and in the end, provided that everything works and the end of the world does not take place...
The anthem will be sung by all the performers at the same time at all three concerts.
In addition, the anthems are broadcast live together on a direct line from Czech TV.
The text of the hymn comes from Tomá<0xC5><0xA1> Hanák, who also plays the main character of Jesus in the video clip, also Xindl X sings with...
How did you come to cooperate with both of them?
We also cooperate with other personalities of the Czech cultural scene, which is related to the fact that we hold many charity events and concerts...
We strive to involve these people intensively in our projects.
It has been shown that most of us are interested in working with us and have fun.
What purpose does the proceeds of concerts against the end of the world benefit?
For the establishment of the barrier-free educational center Studeo, which we have been working on for six years together with the association Tap at the Jedli<0xC4><0x8D>ka Institute.
The students of the Jedli<0xC4><0x8D>ka Institute are regularly supervised by lecturers who help them with various leisure activities.
Since the students themselves do not have the means to visit the readers, we want to help them in this way.
As part of the completion of the Jedli<0xC4><0x8D>ka Institute, we will create our own building, which we will then move into with this project.
At each concert there are several groups and performers.
