The first impression that the viewer usually has is, of course, pity; that is only natural...
But this pity is absolutely superfluous because people with disabilities are not lonely and abandoned beings that we should regret.
They are people who can live and develop a full life, provided they have the necessary means to do so.
I always say that if people with disabilities succeed, it is not only progress for themselves, but for society as a whole.
Was it also helpful for this success that you are a strict boss, as you hear from many people?
