The spirits can suppress the smell.
I tasted some snacks.
If you avoid bringing the Rakfisk near your nose, it is not bad - like sushi, which has a long bus ride behind it.
Rakfisk is the product of a completely different, far poorer Norwegian era, when there were no cooling facilities and fish were soaked in airtight saltwater barrels in the fall.
In the deepest winter, it was then taken out after long fermentation and - undoubtedly with the help of alcohol - consumed.
Just a generation ago, thousands of Norwegians in search of work were forced to leave their country and emigrated mainly to the United States.
