The children can get others.
“It’s important to me to have my own money and time,” says another man, about twenty years old.
Men and women cite their careers, stress, and the cost of ownership and education as reasons that they can’t have children.
That’s why Singaporeans have the last word when it comes to having children – there’s still so much the government can do.
