31 years after the appearance of AIDS in the world, i.e. after the occurrence of the first reported cases, "the great success today means that the survival of a patient who starts treatment on time and the survival of the general population are exactly the same," explained the head of the HIV unit of HCG, Jaime Andrade Villanueva, saying that this information was scientifically considered in April of this year.
