After the U.S. Court of Appeals upheld a ruling not recognizing the restructuring of Vitro Group’s liabilities reached through a commercial bankruptcy in Mexico, a disastrous precedent is set for any national company with offices in the neighboring country that has payment problems.
So one could say that the procedures for the survival of companies that allow Mexican laws are not valid in the land of stars and stripes in contradiction to international agreements.
