While the judge of the case points out that creditors must be subject to U.S. bankruptcy law, the New Orleans-based Fifth Circuit Court of Appeals first says that the main proceeding is the commercial bankruptcy dealt with in Mexico.
The first point would mean that international cooperation in insolvency proceedings of companies with a cross-border profile is not known.
